JOINT RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1 FOR REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION SOURCES SERVICE AMONG CHIEF CONEMAUGH POWER, LLC AND MONTOUR, LLC
Conemaugh Generating Station ("Conemaugh") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Conemaugh generation facility located in New Florence, Pennsylvania and interconnected to the Pennsylvania Electric Company ("Penelec") transmission system, which is under the operational control of PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Joint Rate Schedule sets forth the revenue requirement for two of Conemaugh's owners for Reactive Supply Service from Conemaugh's generation facility to PJM and Penelec.
This Joint Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT
The total Reactive Service Annual Revenue Requirement is $668,288.12, and the total monthly charge is $55,690.68.
THE TOTAL REVENUE REQUIREMENT IS ALLOCATED AS FOLLOWS:
Annual Monthly Chief Conemaugh Power, LLC $262,678.67 $21,889.89 Montour, LLC $405,609.45 $33,800.78

CHIEF CONEMAUGH POWER, LLC
REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE
Chief Conemaugh Power, LLC ("Chief Conemaugh") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from an electric generation facility located in New Florence, Pennsylvania that is interconnected to the transmission system operated by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth Chief Conemaugh's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from the facility pursuant to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Service. Chief Conemaugh also receives additional revenue requirements for the facility pursuant to a separate rate schedule. See Joint Rate Schedule FERC No. 1, most recently accepted by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission on September 1, 2020 in Docket No. ER20-2637-000.
Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Reactive Service Tariff shall be effective on the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The total annual revenue requirement is $95,440.16.
The total monthly revenue requirement is $95,440.16 / 12 = $7,953.34.
